title: Best Mid-Range Smartphones (Summer 2022) | Top 10 Reviewed!
description:
Reviewing the best mid-range Android smartphones of Summer 2022 with the best camera tech, gaming performance and more, for a budget of ¬£400 and under. From the Pixel 6a and Nothing Phone 1 to Samsung's Galaxy A53 5G and Xiaomi's Redmi Note 11 Pro Plus (plus the Poco F4). These are my favourite budget-friendly mid-range phones you can buy in the UK!

If you're after an even cheaper handset, check out my reviews and round-ups of the greatest Android smartphones under ¬£300 and ¬£200 too.

Coming up with my top 10 was quite tricky this far into 2022. Manufacturers like Google, Nothing, Samsung, Xiaomi and Realme all offer a selection of compelling smartphones at a mid-range asking price. The Pixel 6a is still the best around for camera performance but rivals like the OnePlus Nord 2T aren't far behind. Recent additions such as the Nothing Phone 1 are also compelling, with unique features like wireless charging.

That Samsung Galaxy A53 5G is lovable, although the gaming performance isn't as good as last year's A52s, so you may be tempted to look back instead. Meanwhile the Xiaomi Redmi Note 11 Pro Plus is a bit of a mouthful but also a great smartphone, boasting impressive specs for a budget-friendly cost. For less cash you can also grab the Note 11 and regular Pro (check out my full comparison). And that Poco F4 is one of my favourites for gaming grunt.

Realme's excellent 9 Pro Plus and GT Master Edition are also well worth a squint. So many to consider, so which is your personal favourite?

title: Best Mid-Range Smartphones (Early 2023) | Top 15 Reviewed!
description:
Reviewing the top 15 best mid-range Android smartphones in early 2023 with the greatest camera tech, gaming performance and more. These phones suit a budget of ¬£400 and under, with mid range mobiles from the Pixel 6a and Nothing Phone 1 to the Realme 10 Pro Plus and Samsung's Galaxy A53 5G. These are the best budget-friendly mid range smartphones you can buy in the UK!

If you're after an even cheaper handset, check out my reviews and round-ups of the greatest Android smartphones under ¬£300 and ¬£200 too.

Coming up with my top 10 was quite tricky as we hit 2023. Manufacturers like Google, Nothing, Samsung, Xiaomi and Realme all offer a selection of compelling smartphones at a mid-range asking price. The Pixel 6a is still the best around for camera performance but rivals like the OnePlus Nord 2T aren't far behind. Recent additions such as the Realme 10 Pro Plus and Nothing Phone 1 are also compelling, with unique features like wireless charging and curved displays.

That Samsung Galaxy A53 5G is lovable, although the gaming performance isn't as good as last year's A52s, so you may be tempted to look back instead. Meanwhile the Xiaomi Redmi Note 11 Pro Plus is a bit of a mouthful but also a great smartphone, boasting impressive specs for a budget-friendly cost. For less cash you can also grab the Note 11 and regular Pro (check out my full comparison). And that Poco F4 is one of my favourite mid range smartphones in 2023 for gaming grunt, while the Motorola Edge 30 Neo is a compelling choice for small phone fans.

So many handset options to consider, so which is your personal favourite for under ¬£400 here in the UK?

title: TOP 5 Best Compact Powerful Smartphones for 2022 | Best Small Phones 2022 | Pocket Mobiles
description:
TOP 5 Best Compact Powerful Smartphones for 2022 | Best Small Phones 2022 | Pocket Mobiles.
The best small phones have died a slow death. Apple did its part to keep compact phones in people's hands. The company's latest device is the iPhone SE (2022), a new version of the 4.7-inch iPhone that adds a new processor and 5G connectivity. But the iPhone mini line is dead, replaced by the giant iPhone Plus models.

But it's clear the handset doesn't have much company, as smartphone displays continue to get larger and larger. That's fine for people who like big screens, but there are precious few options for those who prefer something they can comfortably use one-handed. Trust us, we think this is quite the tragedy.

A notable advantage to choosing a small phone is that they typically cost less than Plus-, Max- or Ultra-sized versions of the same device, so you won't be penalized by having to pay more for a handset that easily fits into your lifestyle.

title: Best Camera Phones (2024) | Top 12 Ultra Smartphone Shooters
description:
Reviewing the best camera phones in 2024 including the Samsung Galaxy S24 Ultra, Xiaomi 14 Ultra, Pixel 8 Pro and more! These are my favourite smartphones for shooting photos and video, offering slick camera experiences and results. I've tested them all, from that Samsung S24 Ultra to the Honor Magic 6 Pro, Xperia 1 V and Huawei P60 Pro - and you can expect more hot smartphones to launch soon in 2024!

Check out my review of the best budget cameraphones for cheaper alternatives.

Google's flagships are still two of the best camera devices for shooting great looking family photos. The Pixel 8 Pro and regular version can capture slick pics day or night, while the 7a is great on a tighter budget. If you're more into video, check out the iPhone 15 Pro Max or Samsung's Galaxy S24 series, especially the Samsung S24 Ultra. And Xiaomi's latest 14 series phones are ideal for camera lovers, especially the Xiaomi 14 Ultra with its expert video controls.

Last year's Huawei P60 Pro is still easily one of the best camera phones in 2024, although the lack of Google services will put many punters off. And if you like DSLR style Pro controls, check out the Sony Xperia 1 V.

So those are my favourite cameras on any mobiles right now. Did I miss out your pick of the best? Let us know below and check out my reviews of these phones here on Tech Spurt!

title: Best Smartphones 2022 | Top 10+ for Gaming, Camera, Budget & More!
description:
The best smartphones of 2022, tested and reviewed - this year I've personally fondled almost 90 new phones, boasting next-gen camera optics, gaming smarts and battery tech. From the best flagship Android mobiles up to 2023 to my favourite budget smartphones, here's the greatest devices from this year (in my eyes, anyway).

While a lot of handsets in 2022 have been minor evolutions of last year's models, a few have stood out as exceptional. The best camera phone award was a tricky one, because the Pixel 7 Pro, Vivo X80 Pro, Oppo Find X5 Pro etc have all performed impressively. We even saw some 200MP camera smartphones in 2022, including the Motorola Edge 30 Ultra and Xiaomi 12T Pro.

Likewise, this year saw the launch of brilliant budget phones like the Poco X4 Pro and Motorola G82 - plus rivals from OnePlus, Nokia and more. Bump up your price a little and you can get some of my favourite mid-range mobiles, including the Pixel 6a from Google and the slightly mental Nothing Phone 1.

So these are some of the best smartphones of 2022 in my own mind, but did I miss out your favourites? Bear in mind these are phones that aren't limited to China, so I skipped over the Xiaomi 12S Ultra and a few other notable blowers.

My favourite stock Android phones before 2023 include the Google Pixel 7, Pro and 6a, as well as the Nothing Phone 1, Moto G82, Nokia X30 and the Zenfone 9.

Links to best rugged smartphones are listed below. At HowMuchTech, we've researched the best rugged smartphone options on Amazon, saving you time and money.

Key Features of the Best Rugged Smartphones:

Durability: Rugged smartphones are designed to withstand tough conditions. They typically adhere to military-grade standards for durability, ensuring resistance to drops, shocks, vibrations, and extreme temperatures.

IP Ratings: The best rugged smartphones often come with high Ingress Protection (IP) ratings, indicating resistance to water and dust. IP68 is a common rating, ensuring water resistance even when submerged to a certain depth.

Build Quality: Rugged smartphones have reinforced chassis and exteriors, often made from tough materials such as metal or reinforced plastic. Some models may feature rubberized edges for added shock absorption.

Display Protection: These phones often come with toughened glass, such as Gorilla Glass, to protect against scratches and cracks. Some may also have additional layers of screen protection, making them more resistant to impact.

Battery Life: Extended battery life is a crucial feature for users who may be in remote locations without easy access to charging. The best rugged smartphones are designed to last through long workdays or outdoor adventures.

Cameras: While not always a primary focus, rugged smartphones may include decent cameras for documentation purposes. Some models may feature specialized camera enhancements for specific use cases.

Specialized Features: The best-rugged smartphones may have additional features tailored to specific industries or use cases. This can include programmable buttons, glove-friendly touchscreens, and enhanced GPS capabilities.

Connectivity: Rugged smartphones typically support the latest connectivity standards, including 4G and 5G, ensuring users have access to high-speed internet in challenging environments.

Software: Some rugged smartphones come with specialized software or applications designed for specific industries like construction, logistics, or emergency services. Customizable software solutions can enhance the functionality of the phone for specialized tasks.

Brand Reputation: Stick to reputable brands with a history of producing durable and reliable rugged smartphones. Brands with a track record of quality are more likely to deliver on the promise of durability and performance.

When looking for the best-rugged smartphone, consider your specific needs and the environmental conditions it will be exposed to. Reading reviews, checking specifications, and assessing user feedback for the latest models will help you make an informed decision based on your requirements.

Links to best rugged smartphones are listed below. At HowMuchTech, we've researched the best rugged smartphone options on Amazon, saving you time and money.

Key Features of the Best Rugged Smartphones:

Durability: Rugged smartphones are designed to withstand tough conditions. They typically adhere to military-grade standards for durability, ensuring resistance to drops, shocks, vibrations, and extreme temperatures.

IP Ratings: The best rugged smartphones often come with high Ingress Protection (IP) ratings, indicating resistance to water and dust. IP68 is a common rating, ensuring water resistance even when submerged to a certain depth.

Build Quality: Rugged smartphones have reinforced chassis and exteriors, often made from tough materials such as metal or reinforced plastic. Some models may feature rubberized edges for added shock absorption.

Display Protection: These phones often come with toughened glass, such as Gorilla Glass, to protect against scratches and cracks. Some may also have additional layers of screen protection, making them more resistant to impact.

Battery Life: Extended battery life is a crucial feature for users who may be in remote locations without easy access to charging. The best rugged smartphones are designed to last through long workdays or outdoor adventures.

Cameras: While not always a primary focus, rugged smartphones may include decent cameras for documentation purposes. Some models may feature specialized camera enhancements for specific use cases.

Specialized Features: The best-rugged smartphones may have additional features tailored to specific industries or use cases. This can include programmable buttons, glove-friendly touchscreens, and enhanced GPS capabilities.

Connectivity: Rugged smartphones typically support the latest connectivity standards, including 4G and 5G, ensuring users have access to high-speed internet in challenging environments.

Software: Some rugged smartphones come with specialized software or applications designed for specific industries like construction, logistics, or emergency services. Customizable software solutions can enhance the functionality of the phone for specialized tasks.

Brand Reputation: Stick to reputable brands with a history of producing durable and reliable rugged smartphones. Brands with a track record of quality are more likely to deliver on the promise of durability and performance.

When looking for the best-rugged smartphone, consider your specific needs and the environmental conditions it will be exposed to. Reading reviews, checking specifications, and assessing user feedback for the latest models will help you make an informed decision based on your requirements.

title: The SHOCKING Collapse of LG Smartphones: What Went Wrong?
description:
The Epic Rise & Fall LG Smartphones
Embark on an emotional journey through the epic rise and fall of LG's smartphones. Once a trailblazer in the Android world, LG pushed the boundaries of mobile technology, from the groundbreaking LG Prada to the captivating LG G3. But even with a history of daring innovation, LG's smartphone division ultimately became an afterthought. In this video, we explore the unforgettable highs and heartbreaking lows of LG's smartphone saga. Discover how fierce competition, poor marketing, quality issues, and a lack of focus led to the downfall of a once-iconic brand.

Join the TechSquad for bonuses: http://youtube.com/gearlive/join

As we pay tribute to LG's legacy, uncover the invaluable lessons that the smartphone industry can learn from their story. Remember the iconic devices like the LG Nexus, G Flex, and Wing that revolutionized the smartphone experience. Delve into the mistakes and missteps that led to LG's eventual exit from the market, making way for giants like Samsung and Apple. The story of LG's smartphones is one of ambition, risk-taking, and the pursuit of excellence, as well as the cost of failure and the importance of learning from mistakes.

Join us as we celebrate the legacy of a company that dared to dream, create, and inspire. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe for more in-depth looks at the tech industry's most intriguing stories.
